[7.11.22]

WHY?        To train community health leaders

HOW?        By empowering people to experientially restore foot health, leading a workshop, and conneting them with a global network of health leaders

WHAT?       A time commitment of 1 hour a day for 12 weeks, a financial commitment of $1,600 usd

-------
 [from Ruth: 7.11.22]
 
After you complete 12 weeks of Foot Nerd Training: 
- You become a member of a global Foot Nerd network: An opportunity to collaborate, discuss and debate ideas with the people who are the most dedicated and focused on this topic
- You have lifetime access to all the digital content we've created together so far and all the content we create in the future. 
- You will have created your own workshop manual specific to your community and needs, have ongoing support and exposure to over 300,000 + people when we broadcast your events.



[7.7.22]

--

Why did we create Foot Nerd training? 

To train people who lead by example and can effectively others restore health starting with the feet

--

How does Foot Nerd training accomplish that? 

By guiding people through 12 weeks of learning, doing and reflecting which culminates with proof of work submission and earning income from
delivering a foot health workshop in their community

--

What is Foot Nerd training?

12 weeks of experiential training

A time commitment of 1 hour a day for 12 consecutive weeks

A financial commitment of $1,600 usd

--



